#!ek9
<?-
  Literal Validation Fuzz Test: Money - Overflow Amount Value
  Tests if EK9 catches extreme monetary amount at compile time.

  Expected: Should fail (amount value causes overflow in underlying representation)
  Actual: Compiles successfully, becomes unset at runtime
-?>
defines module fuzz.literal.money.overflow
  defines program
    Test()
      m <- 99999999999999.99#USD
      stdout <- Stdout()
      if m?
        stdout.println("Set")
//EOF
